Manchester United have offered striker, Alexis Sanchez, to Borussia Dortmund in a swap deal for their winger, Jadon Sancho, according to Mundo Deportivo. Man United are eager to offload Sanchez, who is currently out on loan at Serie A giant, Inter Milan. DAILY POST recalls that Sancho had drawn the interest of Man United in the past. Man United are willing to offer Sancho the no.7 shirt, in a bid to lure him to join the Red Devils this summer transfer window. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s side are believed to be leading the race to sign the England youngster from Dortmund for a club-record fee. Sancho has netted 17 goals and registered 18 assists in 39 appearances for Dortmund so far this season. The 20-year-old is valued at over £100million by his Bundesliga club and United will have to battle Premier League rivals, Chelsea and Liverpool for his signature. Sancho has two years left on his current deal at Dortmund. EPL: Berbatov gives reason Jadon Sancho wouldn't think twice to join Man Utd EPL: Emre Can advises Jadon Sancho against leaving Dortmund for Man Utd EPL: Marcus Rashford welcomes Sancho to Man Utd